|footnotes = }} Winner is a city in the southern part of the U.S. state of South Dakota. It is the county seat of Tripp County, and it also administrates nearby Todd County, which does not have a county seat. It became a city in 1911, and 2,921 people lived there at the 2020 census. ==References== ==Other websites== *City of Winner website Category:County seats in South Dakota Category:Cities in South Dakota Category:1911 establishments in South Dakota
